<br>
However, they did.<br>
<br>
Just yesterday I was clearing a path down to the library in Kaesora to get a VP key bit, using Dyzil's Deafing Decoy to gather up 4 or 5 Minions of Xalgoz to chew themselves on his DS.  Let the skellies beat themselves down a bit and BAM - Scintillation!  Its fun to do it while in third person view and see them all die at once.<br>
<br>
I have used my PBAE on XP mobs during Chardok royals raids.  New PBAE spells could be conceivably used during PoJ trials.<br>
<br>
In any case the point remains, regardless of the continued viability of AE XP groups, what was the thought process behind granting upgrades to Clerics and Druids but deliberately leaving mages out?<br>
